The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 Mohun Bagans Brazilian striker Jose Ramirez Barreto decided to stay with the club for another season. Besides Barreto, goalkeeper Sangram Mukherjee, forwards P.C. Lalwmpuia and Rahul Kumar also withdrew at the IFA office. Arch-rivals East Bengal also signed Dharamjit Singh and Abhra Mondal on the day.           
	 Anindita Chakraborty, Anushree Saha, Gargi Nag, Subham Chowdhury and Soumyajit Sarkar will participate in the North Calcutta District Table Tennis championship to be held from Wednesday. The four-day long meet, is a state ranking tournament with a total prize money of Rs 15,000.          
	 The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) finance committee after a meeting on Monday decided to increase the daily allowances of its umpires from Rs 240 to Rs 325. The CABs annual prize distribution will be held on July 29.                                                                                                                                                                     
